The paper focuses on developing a neural network structure for solving video question and answering task, which involves understanding the content or story of the video. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a squeeze-and-excitation structure and a context matching module with attention mechanism, which are commonly used in deep learning models for image and text processing, respectively. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
